INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE POINT CLOUD:

You need a quadrotor with kinect or asus xtion to see point cloud (quadrotor with asus xtion used in here)

1. Run the command below to open rviz
	$ rosrun rviz rviz
2. After running the codes, on the display part in rviz choose the frame id as the id that you arrange in these codes it is "camera_link"

3. On the display part push the "Add" button and choose the "PointCloud2"

4. In the PointCloud2 part choose the topic that is related with your point cloud data in this case it is "/camera/depth/points"

5. Then you should see the point cloud in camera frame. you can choose the frame that you interested in.
